node.title: Yoga to Self Soothe During Periods of Mental/Emotional Distress

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 16, 2021 tagging @tanner_hamilton22. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
My anxiety always plays tricks on me…constantly making me think up the worst scenarios. Following people like @anxietyjosh have helped me tremendously. Managing anxiety is hard to do and if you live with it every day just know I think you are so brave and I’m so proud of you for continuing to fight the good fight against it. Some things that have helped me with my anxiety are therapy, grounding techniques along with being honest with my friends and family about things that give me anxiety or triggers and getting reassurance from them when I feel anxiety. I think one thing I failed at doing was telling people “I don’t feel comfortable doing that, it’s going to make me feel anxious”. Once I set that boundary with people, it changed my life. I hope you all have an amazing day. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#anxiety #anxietyattack #anxietyawareness #anxietyrelief #anxiousmoments #panicattack #panicattacks #panicdisorder #keepgoing #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #keepgoing #ialwaysfeelanxiety #curveyouranxiety

May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'adhd-angsty @AdhdAngsty Me: 'I'm not impulsive" Also me: wants to quit after one bad work day, says yes to plans that can't make, spends $$$ on hyperfocuses, stays up late despite chronic illness, accidentally starts arguments with partner and family, drinks too much at parties etc etc etc'.

node.text:
I am impulsive AF. 

I’m not clinically diagnosed with any mental health problems, so I won’t call myself someone with ADHD or OCD, but I know I’m prone to the traits of someone diagnosed with those mental health issues. 

Thankfully now that I don’t drink anymore ( eight years sober 🤟🏽) my impulsivity is more manageable. Im more aware when I overspend, or get in random arguments with people on the internet over basically nothing. I’m trying to set boundaries for myself and limit this impulsive behavior. 

How do you calm yourself the fuck down? @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @adhdangsty
.
.
.
.
.
#suicideawarenessmonth #anxiety #adhd #obsessivecompulsive #mentalhealthmeme🖤#asafeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 15, 2021 tagging @tanner_hamilton22. May be a meme of text that says 'When you suffer from depression and somebody tells you to just cheer up.. My goodness, what an idea. Why didn't I think of that ?'.

node.text:
Posted this on my personal and thought more people may need to see this….if you are helping someone do you best to not say “cheer up” because it’s definitely the wrong way to approach the situation in my opinion. Sometimes I just need to vent and want someone to listen, I don’t really even need advice. I just need to hear the words outside of my head if that makes sense. Anyways, this made me laugh really hard cause it’s low key true so I hope you get a chuckle out of it. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.

.
.
.
.

node.text:
TW: Suicide 

Just some healthy things I had to tell myself when I hit my darkest times, I don’t know who made this list but I saved it to my phone a few years ago and still reference it on some bad day. You are so worthy of the love you will receive. Life is hard but we have to keep going, we owe it to ourselves to see it through to the other side. As morbid as it sounds, I think of the things I’ll miss if I take my own life and it keeps me going. I don’t want my daughter being alone in her milestones in life so I’m going to fight every day to stay alive. - @tanner_hamilton22

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 13, 2021 tagging @drjenpsych_. May be an image of text that says 'Dr. Jen (Wolkin) @drjenpsych_ What didn' kill you didn't make you stronger. What didn't kill you *cked with your sense of safety, unraveled your trust, left you shaking, forgetful, dissociated, numb, and @drjenpsych_ sleepless. YOU made yourself stonger+ survived. It was YOU.'.

node.text:
It’s not the event or trauma that makes you stronger, it’s your reaction to it. 

My sons suicide death filled me with grief, but my reaction to reach out and help others so no other mother or family member  or friend has to feel my pain, that’s where the strength came. 

Deciding to end my relationship with alcohol and live my life on life’s terms was the event, but the strength comes in me, every day just for today, making the decision NOT to pick up that drink. 

It’s hard to give yourself a pat on the back for the good work you’ve done. But I’m here to say I’m proud of me and I am proud of you and the progress you’ve made. 

It’s you, just you and all you, every damn day, you are the power. 

Thank you for coming to my Ted talk 🤟🏽 - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @drjenpsych_ 
.
.
.
.
.

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Kira J @lamKiraJ QបL Y'all be beating yourself up about the mistakes you've made in the past as if you been here twice or something. This is your first time living this life. Give yourself some grace as you've learned to navigate through it. You don't know what you don't know til you know better.'.

node.text:
It’s hard to give yourself grace when you mess up. It’s had to say it’s ok, when you’ve failed at something you wanted to succeed at. 

Mistakes are proof that you are trying. Mistakes are not failures but steps to success. 

Now if you keep making the same mistake over and over, that’s on you. But trying and failing, or stumbling, it’s all part of the steps that we take in this dance called living. - @therealjoirizarry 

“I’m not perfect, but I’m always real”  @2pac 

📸 @iamkiraj on Twitter 
.

Today I’m feeling especially antisocial. 

Being able to distance my self physically but still being socially active in my own cocoon is the shit. 

I’m sure this behavior isn’t great for my mental health, but I’m gonna do it anyway, just for today. 

Some days I need physical space from peopling, and today I will honor it. - @therealjoirizarry
